<font color="#FF0000">A MATTER OF CHOICE</font><br>
<tt>Fri Oct 10 20:23:30 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
If the requirement to post here is the agreement and or acceptance of everyone's views then we have no need for dialogue.  If the feeling of rejection for  points not accepted causes departure then no one would be left.<br><br>
The sense of humility that every vet has felt seems to be too much for those of lessor conviction.  If Class Lass is true to her name she will stay and continue her point of view, as will we.  It matters little if we agree or not.  It is her right.  We all agree on that point.<br><br>
Do not ever assume that a cheap shot whether real or perceived or will go unanswered.  &quot;A matter of Honor&quot;.<br><br>
Shall we draft the rules of engagement?  Would it do any good?  Probably not.<br><br>
One rule.  No whining.  It isn't dignified.<br>

